summary: An automated email notification from the DOJ's E2 Solutions travel system indicating that a final travel voucher (ID 10894369(1)) is pending review. The voucher is for travel to Santa Monica, CA from December 15-17, 2019, related to the case 'U.S. v. Epstein - Witness Interviews'.

events.title: Witness Interview Travel to Santa Monica
events.description: Travel occurred to Santa Monica, CA for the purpose of conducting witness interviews for the U.S. v. Epstein case.

keyFacts: The document is a travel voucher notification from the DOJ's internal E2 Solutions system.
The travel (Trip ID 10894369) was for the specific purpose 'R20NYS13261 - U.S. v. Epstein - Witness Interviews'.
The travel destination was Santa Monica, CA from December 15 to December 17, 2019.
The voucher total expenses were $1,296.43 against an estimated trip cost of $1,662.95.
The notification was sent on January 7, 2020, indicating post-travel administrative review.
